{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-13",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_13_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 13 - The Emperor's Gift",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 5,
  "page_start_sec": 250.688,
  "page_end_sec": 505.5,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.673,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 250.688,
      "end": 251.52,
      "text": "That is history,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 251.6,
      "end": 251.78,
      "text": "sir."
    },
    {
      "start": 253.08,
      "end": 255.22,
      "text": "We all know that the holy wars to them,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 255.3,
      "end": 256.5,
      "text": "as to the Templars,"
    },
    {
      "start": 256.62,
      "end": 258.12,
      "text": "were largely a matter of loot."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.08,
      "end": 259.5,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 259.54,
      "end": 259.82,
      "text": "now,"
    },
    {
      "start": 260.3,
      "end": 262.18,
      "text": "the Emperor Charles had given them Malta,"
    },
    {
      "start": 262.32,
      "end": 263.38,
      "text": "and all the rent,"
    },
    {
      "start": 263.48,
      "end": 263.86,
      "text": "he asks,"
    },
    {
      "start": 264.0,
      "end": 266.34,
      "text": "is one insignificant bird per annum,"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.4,
      "end": 268.22,
      "text": "just as a matter of form."
    },
    {
      "start": 269.312,
      "end": 271.04,
      "text": "What could be more natural than for these",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 271.17,
      "end": 273.16,
      "text": "immeasurably wealthy knights to look around"
    },
    {
      "start": 273.3,
      "end": 274.96,
      "text": "for some way of showing their gratitude?"
    },
    {
      "start": 275.62,
      "end": 276.32,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 276.44,
      "end": 276.68,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 276.82,
      "end": 278.72,
      "text": "that's exactly what they did,"
    },
    {
      "start": 278.82,
      "end": 281.5,
      "text": "and they hit on the happy thought of sending Charles,"
    },
    {
      "start": 282.08,
      "end": 283.26,
      "text": "for the first year's tribute,"
    },
    {
      "start": 283.44,
      "end": 285.74,
      "text": "not an insignificant live-bird,"
    },
    {
      "start": 285.9,
      "end": 287.42,
      "text": "but a glorious falcon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 287.78,
      "end": 291.16,
      "text": "encrusted from head to foot with the finest jewels in their coffers."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.64,
      "end": 293.14,
      "text": "And remember,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 293.78,
      "end": 294.74,
      "text": "they had fine ones,"
    },
    {
      "start": 295.14,
      "end": 296.44,
      "text": "the finest out of Asia."
    },
    {
      "start": 297.92,
      "end": 298.92,
      "text": "Gutman stopped whispering.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 299.76,
      "end": 300.2,
      "text": "His sleek,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 300.26,
      "end": 302.26,
      "text": "dark eyes examined Spade's face,"
    },
    {
      "start": 302.42,
      "end": 303.24,
      "text": "which was placid."
    },
    {
      "start": 303.44,
      "end": 304.98,
      "text": "The fat man asked,"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.36,
      "end": 305.9,
      "text": "Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.96,
      "end": 306.24,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 306.38,
      "end": 307.6,
      "text": "what do you think of that?"
    },
    {
      "start": 308.36,
      "end": 309.52,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 310.3,
      "end": 311.62,
      "text": "The fat man smiled.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 312.832,
      "end": 313.64,
      "text": "These are facts,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 313.84,
      "end": 314.96,
      "text": "historical facts."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.7,
      "end": 316.98,
      "text": "Not school-book history,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 317.16,
      "end": 317.92,
      "text": "not Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.06,
      "end": 318.8,
      "text": "Wells's history,"
    },
    {
      "start": 318.96,
      "end": 320.18,
      "text": "but history nonetheless."
    },
    {
      "start": 321.56,
      "end": 322.68,
      "text": "He leaned forward.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 324.24,
      "end": 325.9,
      "text": "The archives of the Order from the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 325.9,
      "end": 327.9,
      "text": "twelfth century are still on Malta."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.28,
      "end": 330.24,
      "text": "They are not intact,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 330.48,
      "end": 333.04,
      "text": "but what is there holds no less than three"
    },
    {
      "start": 333.48,
      "end": 334.86,
      "text": "he held up three fingers,"
    },
    {
      "start": 335.06,
      "end": 339.14,
      "text": "references that can't be to anything else but this jeweled falcon."
    },
    {
      "start": 340.5,
      "end": 340.84,
      "text": "In J.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 340.94,
      "end": 343.38,
      "text": "Delavie de la Rue's Les Archives de l"
    },
    {
      "start": 343.38,
      "end": 346.26,
      "text": "'Ordre de Saint-Jean there is a reference to it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 346.784,
      "end": 347.6,
      "text": "oblique to be sure,"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.82,
      "end": 349.18,
      "text": "but still a reference."
    },
    {
      "start": 349.42,
      "end": 351.78,
      "text": "And the unpublished,"
    },
    {
      "start": 351.88,
      "end": 353.48,
      "text": "because unfinished at the time"
    },
    {
      "start": 353.48,
      "end": 354.0,
      "text": "of his death,"
    },
    {
      "start": 354.16,
      "end": 356.8,
      "text": "supplement to Paoli's Del Origine et"
    },
    {
      "start": 356.8,
      "end": 359.24,
      "text": "Instituto del Sacro Militar Ordine,"
    },
    {
      "start": 359.42,
      "end": 360.46,
      "text": "has a clear"
    },
    {
      "start": 360.66,
      "end": 363.744,
      "text": "an unmistakable statement of these facts I am telling you.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 364.88,
      "end": 366.2,
      "text": "\"'All right,' Spade said.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 367.74,
      "end": 368.14,
      "text": "\"'All right.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 368.26,
      "end": 372.98,
      "text": "Grand Master Villiers de Lille-Dadam had this foot-high jeweled bird"
    },
    {
      "start": 373.24,
      "end": 376.22,
      "text": "made by Turkish slaves in the castle of San Angelo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 376.4,
      "end": 377.86,
      "text": "and sent it to Charles,"
    },
    {
      "start": 378.06,
      "end": 379.12,
      "text": "who was in Spain."
    },
    {
      "start": 380.02,
      "end": 382.22,
      "text": "He sent it in a galley commanded by a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 382.22,
      "end": 384.62,
      "text": "French knight named Cormier or Corvair,"
    },
    {
      "start": 385.16,
      "end": 386.37,
      "text": "a member of the Order.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 387.6,
      "end": 389.14,
      "text": "His voice dropped to a whisper again.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 389.52,
      "end": 391.66,
      "text": "It never reached Spain."
    },
    {
      "start": 392.38,
      "end": 394.92,
      "text": "He smiled with compressed lips and asked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 395.54,
      "end": 397.12,
      "text": "You know of Barbossa,"
    },
    {
      "start": 397.36,
      "end": 398.08,
      "text": "Redbeard,"
    },
    {
      "start": 398.18,
      "end": 399.16,
      "text": "Carradine?"
    },
    {
      "start": 399.62,
      "end": 400.38,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 401.62,
      "end": 404.28,
      "text": "A famous admiral of buccaneers sailing out of Algiers,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 404.32,
      "end": 404.54,
      "text": "then."
    },
    {
      "start": 405.24,
      "end": 405.56,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 405.58,
      "end": 405.8,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 405.94,
      "end": 409.24,
      "text": "he took the knight's galley and he took the bird."
    },
    {
      "start": 410.32,
      "end": 411.52,
      "text": "The bird went to Algiers.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 412.384,
      "end": 413.22,
      "text": "That's a fact.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 414.56,
      "end": 417.16,
      "text": "It's a fact that the French historian Pierre Dan",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 417.48,
      "end": 419.44,
      "text": "put in one of his letters from Algiers."
    },
    {
      "start": 420.2,
      "end": 423.46,
      "text": "He wrote that the bird had been there for more than a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 423.62,
      "end": 424.18,
      "text": "hundred years,"
    },
    {
      "start": 424.44,
      "end": 427.7,
      "text": "and that it had been carried away by Sir Francis Verney,"
    },
    {
      "start": 427.88,
      "end": 429.6,
      "text": "an English adventurer who"
    },
    {
      "start": 429.76,
      "end": 432.9,
      "text": "was with the Algerian buccaneers for a while when he left Algiers."
    },
    {
      "start": 433.92,
      "end": 434.66,
      "text": "Maybe he wasn't,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 434.68,
      "end": 435.42,
      "text": "but Pierre Dan"
    },
    {
      "start": 435.54,
      "end": 435.98,
      "text": "believed it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 436.06,
      "end": 437.54,
      "text": "and that's good enough for me."
    },
    {
      "start": 438.96,
      "end": 440.68,
      "text": "There's nothing said about the bird in Lady",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 440.86,
      "end": 442.96,
      "text": "Francis Verney's Memoirs of the Verney"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.96,
      "end": 444.66,
      "text": "Family during the seventeenth century."
    },
    {
      "start": 445.64,
      "end": 446.0,
      "text": "I looked,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 446.36,
      "end": 449.38,
      "text": "and it's pretty certain that Sir Francis didn't"
    },
    {
      "start": 449.38,
      "end": 451.52,
      "text": "have the bird when he died in a Messina hospital"
    },
    {
      "start": 451.52,
      "end": 452.7,
      "text": "in 1615."
    },
    {
      "start": 453.9,
      "end": 454.88,
      "text": "He was stone-broke."
    },
    {
      "start": 455.12,
      "end": 455.22,
      "text": "But,"
    },
    {
      "start": 455.8,
      "end": 456.08,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 456.16,
      "end": 459.14,
      "text": "there's no denying that the falcon did go to Sicily."
    },
    {
      "start": 460.38,
      "end": 461.06,
      "text": "It was there,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 461.2,
      "end": 463.4,
      "text": "and it came into the possession of Victor"
    },
    {
      "start": 463.4,
      "end": 466.42,
      "text": "Amadeus II sometime after he became king"
    },
    {
      "start": 466.7,
      "end": 467.62,
      "text": "in 1713,"
    },
    {
      "start": 468.2,
      "end": 470.72,
      "text": "and it was one of his gifts to his wife"
    },
    {
      "start": 470.72,
      "end": 473.2,
      "text": "when he married in Chebari after abdicating."
    },
    {
      "start": 474.144,
      "end": 475.0,
      "text": "That is a fact,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 475.1,
      "end": 475.24,
      "text": "sir."
    },
    {
      "start": 475.88,
      "end": 475.98,
      "text": "Carudi,"
    },
    {
      "start": 477.16,
      "end": 480.78,
      "text": "the author of Storia del Regno de Vittoria Amadeo II,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 481.15,
      "end": 482.06,
      "text": "vouched for it."
    },
    {
      "start": 483.936,
      "end": 484.42,
      "text": "Maybe they,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 484.7,
      "end": 485.76,
      "text": "he and his wife,"
    },
    {
      "start": 485.92,
      "end": 489.18,
      "text": "took it along with them to Turin when he tried to revoke his"
    },
    {
      "start": 489.38,
      "end": 489.64,
      "text": "abdication."
    },
    {
      "start": 490.04,
      "end": 491.68,
      "text": "Anyhow,"
    },
    {
      "start": 491.82,
      "end": 493.56,
      "text": "it turned up next in the possession"
    },
    {
      "start": 493.56,
      "end": 495.56,
      "text": "of a Spaniard who had been with the"
    },
    {
      "start": 495.72,
      "end": 497.63,
      "text": "army that took Naples in 1734,"
    },
    {
      "start": 498.9,
      "end": 501.32,
      "text": "the father of Don José Munino y Redondo,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 501.64,
      "end": 502.96,
      "text": "Count of Florida Blanca,"
    },
    {
      "start": 503.2,
      "end": 505.5,
      "text": "who was Charles III's chief minister."
    }
  ]
}